  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>Of Persons Varieties.</head>
   <l>THe Lawyer here may learne Divinity,</l>
   <l>The Divine, Lawes, or faire Astrology;</l>
   <l>The Dammaret respectively to fight,</l>
   <l>The Duellist to court a Mistresse right;</l>
   <l>
      <pb facs="5"/>
Such who their name take from the Rosie-Crosse</l>
   <l>May here by Time, learne to repaire their losse:</l>
   <l>All learne may somewhat, if they be not fooles</l>
   <l>Arts quicklier here are lesson'd, than in Schooles.</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Distich,</hi> of the same.</l>
   <l>This Booke a World is; here if errours be,</l>
   <l>The like (nay worse) in the great world we see.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>William Drummond,
<hi>Of</hi> Hathorn-den.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
